Dialogue: 0,0:41:44.07,0:41:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Meerkat Manor is on Friday night on the animal planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.57,0:41:53.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Meerkat Manor is following these meerkats in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.85,0:41:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatchamacallit desert there.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.05,0:41:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,But the meerkats are very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.17,0:42:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they have a very neat way of being.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.17,0:42:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And each one has sort of a assigned function.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.47,0:42:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But they hang together as a group.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.79,0:42:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's one meerkat culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.03,0:42:15.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And then there's a rival meerkat culture that lives across the field, across the desert.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.51,0:42:17.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Across the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.12,0:42:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And these meerkats are constantly in rivalry.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.86,0:42:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to grab the other one's territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.84,0:42:28.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can't survive without a nice safe place for their little baby meerkats.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.94,0:42:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway, they have to defend their territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.00,0:42:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And so they posted one guy to be on guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.00,0:42:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,These meerkats were off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.29,0:42:37.29,Default,,0,0,0,,These were off here.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.29,0:42:39.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And this guy was supposed to be on guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.29,0:42:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But he was lazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.29,0:42:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,He left his post.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.29,0:42:49.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Left his post and then the other meerkats came in and started grabbing their territory.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.29,0:42:51.45,Default,,0,0,0,,So there you see humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.45,0:42:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Current civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.45,0:42:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you could call one of the clans of meerkats.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:55.52,0:42:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call them in Africa?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.52,0:42:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Meerkats.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.52,0:42:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Meerkats.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.34,0:43:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you could call them in Iraq.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.34,0:43:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The Winnies and the Wooeys.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.34,0:43:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,What are the two?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.62,0:43:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.69,0:43:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.01,0:43:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the Shiites and the Shuwites.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.01,0:43:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Shiites and the...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.32,0:43:15.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:15.06,0:43:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the recapitulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.06,0:43:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And current neuroscience thinks that morality is hardwired into the anatomy and physiology of the nervous system.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.06,0:43:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't find any place out there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.18,0:43:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean in the animal kingdom that morality doesn't apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:37.18,0:43:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You certainly see it in the wolf pack.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.18,0:43:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the struggle for the alpha male, the alpha female.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.18,0:43:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The struggle for dominance and hegemony.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.18,0:43:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It's hegemony.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.82,0:43:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's certain philosophers who don't calibrate very high who like to try to condemn it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.92,0:44:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a basic law of life throughout nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.92,0:44:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,One tends to dominate the other.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.11,0:44:10.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The strongest country will dominate as far as it can dominate.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.21,0:44:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.21,0:44:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's the nature of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.21,0:44:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So somehow survival and morality right and wrong are like inborn, wired into the nervous system.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.40,0:44:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Right versus wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.85,0:44:30.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And a society that tries to reverse right versus wrong
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.85,0:44:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,will go through a period of great confusion and collapse
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.85,0:44:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because now it's trying to change the identifications of right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.94,0:44:45.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And we see that in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.97,0:44:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,What was right in 1950 is now old hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.97,0:44:52.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Old hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:52.03,0:44:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no longer necessary to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.90,0:44:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,No longer necessary to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.90,0:45:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The only thing that's important is don't get caught in a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.99,0:45:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Right versus wrong then is hardwired into human and animal life.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.82,0:45:19.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And the birth of morality, you would have to say it's somewhere back in history many millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.85,0:45:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Many millions of years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.85,0:45:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Those organisms that live at the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.12,0:45:32.66,Default,,0,0,0,,It guards its place there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.66,0:45:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,God help any other scuttlefish that tries to get in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:34.66,0:45:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I'm squirting with black ink. Get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.99,0:45:44.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Chasing away.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:44.99,0:45:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the morality is on a certain level primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.60,0:45:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,On a certain level primitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.60,0:45:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,At its highest level of very advanced spiritual understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.60,0:45:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.92,0:46:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Right versus wrong and the birth of morality is intrinsic within the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.92,0:46:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Now all the definitions of these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.92,0:46:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.92,0:46:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's not real.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.92,0:46:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.92,0:46:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.92,0:46:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.92,0:46:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So not only is it constantly changing.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:15.92,0:46:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It changes with the decade.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.92,0:46:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It changes with the media.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.92,0:46:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,But it changes throughout life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.92,0:46:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What's right and wrong in infancy now won't do that in childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.92,0:46:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Which again won't do that in adolescence.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.92,0:46:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Which won't do that in adulthood.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.92,0:46:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is no longer appropriate in middle age.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.14,0:46:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,And no longer appropriate in old age.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.33,0:46:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So a person here who imitates this kind of behavior or these values would look idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.90,0:46:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're expected to not only master all these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.90,0:46:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You're supposed to show an evolution of your comprehension and your behaviors to reflect this.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.90,0:46:59.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And this of course is where education.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.90,0:47:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Education is supposed to be of great help.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.90,0:47:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How to be doddering and not let it bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.95,0:47:11.95,Default,,0,0,0,,How to not complain about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.95,0:47:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,All of these things now change depending on the state of sickness or health.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:18.87,0:47:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sickness or health you automatically can excuse a lot of these roles.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.87,0:47:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you're sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.87,0:47:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore these duties.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.87,0:47:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,These obligations.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.87,0:47:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Right versus wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.87,0:47:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Suddenly changes its definition.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.87,0:47:38.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Common agreement on all of these things brings about social accord.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.22,0:47:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And enables governance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.22,0:47:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Without agreement there's difficulty.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.22,0:47:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Not impossibility of governance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.22,0:47:48.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And what changes the whole picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.41,0:47:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you think you've got this all down pat.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.41,0:47:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then comes politicalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.41,0:47:59.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the definitions of right and wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.05,0:48:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What's moral.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.05,0:48:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What's appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.05,0:48:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer to all the things of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.05,0:48:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Are now re-edited.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.05,0:48:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So politicalization is a way of constantly re-editing everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.05,0:48:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And in our today's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.30,0:48:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.30,0:48:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a blue light or there's a red light I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.30,0:48:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,And everything that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.30,0:48:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can shine a blue light or a red light.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.30,0:48:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And that says whether you're right or left.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:25.34,0:48:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Politicalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.34,0:48:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So right and wrong is now politicalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.34,0:48:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So that all these definitions of what's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.34,0:48:34.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's valuable.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.34,0:48:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's worthwhile.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.34,0:48:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,What's moral.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.34,0:48:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Now can be completely redefined by politicalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.37,0:48:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What's popularized.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.85,0:48:45.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.85,0:48:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now depends on bloggerism more than anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.98,0:48:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So we used to have God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.98,0:48:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we got bloggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.98,0:48:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to worry about pleasing God.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.98,0:49:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now we worry that we might offend some bloggers.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.98,0:49:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So whole political parties go to a convention.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.14,0:49:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And some they don't really believe in.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.23,0:49:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're scared that the bloggers will be after them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.23,0:49:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have manipulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.23,0:49:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We have manipulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.23,0:49:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We have manipulation via the fear of hate.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.23,0:49:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Hatred is a new manipulative tool.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:19.26,0:49:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not just fear of destruction.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.26,0:49:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But hatred itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.30,0:49:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So by threatening or utilizing the tools of hatred now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.49,0:49:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything has become politicalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.62,0:49:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The language.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.62,0:49:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The words.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.62,0:49:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Every inflection and gesture now becomes politicalized.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.67,0:49:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to be careful how you phrase things.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.67,0:49:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you use one wrong word.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.67,0:49:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And there you've just had it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.67,0:49:52.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have a dictatorship now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.02,0:49:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,By bloggerized hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.22,0:49:59.95,Default,,0,0,0,,We used to be afraid of the Nazi totalitarian.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.95,0:50:01.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese imperialism.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.95,0:50:08.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now what everybody's afraid of is negative hate bloggerism.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.43,0:50:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Which have replaced the world's religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.85,0:50:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.85,0:50:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It's how you're bloggerized.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.04,0:50:20.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The impact of the world's religions of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.04,0:50:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We've gone through extensively in previous lectures.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:23.04,0:50:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And they are still extremely dominant.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.04,0:50:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,They are also dominant also by negation.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.04,0:50:32.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact you don't believe in any of the world's great religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.04,0:50:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it becomes secularism.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.04,0:50:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we have instead of world religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.04,0:50:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We have world non-religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.04,0:50:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's either the presence or absence of religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.04,0:50:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,That signifies a change of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.04,0:50:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,As we said all the levels above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.10,0:50:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact enlightenment itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.19,0:50:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Can be reached by following the Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.19,0:51:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The Sermon on the Mount is actually a political statement.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.51,0:51:05.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a new book called The Political Teachings of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.58,0:51:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Political Teachings of Jesus.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.86,0:51:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And what it really amounts to is the Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:10.86,0:51:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And its social applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.86,0:51:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Social applications.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.96,0:51:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Significance.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.96,0:51:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Significance and meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.06,0:51:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Of the Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.12,0:51:21.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So all a person has to do then.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.12,0:51:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to end up in a good place at the end of this whole trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.18,0:51:27.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Is study the Sermon on the Mount.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.18,0:51:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Apply it in your daily life.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.38,0:51:32.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Follow the Ten Commandments.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.44,0:51:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And avoid the ten greatly.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.50,0:51:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it ten deadly sins?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.76,0:51:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Seven?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.76,0:51:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't jump around me did they?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.01,0:51:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, I hope it's only seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.22,0:51:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.48,0:51:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep the Ten Commandments.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.48,0:51:49.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And avoid the seven deadly sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:49.48,0:51:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Sermon on the Mount pretty much covers it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.48,0:51:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,For everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.48,0:51:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Including Buddhists.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.48,0:51:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And anybody else who is spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.48,0:51:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It was Christ that said it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:58.48,0:52:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,But to love your fellow man as yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.48,0:52:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To serve.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.80,0:52:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Become the greatest that you can become.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.80,0:52:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To serve your fellow man.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.80,0:52:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And God is all that anyone can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.80,0:52:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,As you understand God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.38,0:52:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So the huge impact of the world religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.38,0:52:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,We could spend the whole rest of the year talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.38,0:52:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And each one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.38,0:52:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one of them has a fascinating history.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.38,0:52:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you have the divisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.50,0:52:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is supposed to be divisive.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:27.66,0:52:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Divisiveness of races.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.66,0:52:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.66,0:52:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And nationalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.66,0:52:33.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To make this all complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.66,0:52:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All this applies in very different ways.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.66,0:52:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Depending on your nationality.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.66,0:52:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The color of your skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.66,0:52:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,They forgot your sexual orientation.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.66,0:52:46.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.97,0:52:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.97,0:52:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Has to be completely changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.97,0:52:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,If you change gender.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.97,0:52:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the education and the IQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.98,0:53:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Add another layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.98,0:53:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see how complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.98,0:53:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Trying to understand human behavior is now.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.98,0:53:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We're piling mirrors upon mirrors upon mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.98,0:53:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All the original questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.98,0:53:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So all the underlying reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.98,0:53:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The politicalizations then.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.98,0:53:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course you're impacted by the profound influence.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.98,0:53:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Of all the world's religions.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.98,0:53:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You can hardly underestimate.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.10,0:53:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what a secular person does in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:25.10,0:53:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,In the United States of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.10,0:53:29.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Seeing as the entire constitution.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.10,0:53:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Bill of rights and everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.10,0:53:33.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The rule of law.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.10,0:53:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is based on a world religion.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.33,0:53:37.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So then you get.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.33,0:53:39.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Internal conflict.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.62,0:53:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Over who's going to have.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.62,0:53:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.62,0:53:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So here's the power struggle.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.62,0:53:47.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Which you see throughout the animal kingdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:47.62,0:53:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So please.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:49.62,0:53:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.62,0:53:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So politicalization then.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:52.62,0:53:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Is a sophisticated way.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.62,0:53:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Of seeing.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.62,0:53:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The animal conflict that goes on between.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.62,0:54:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The meerkats.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.62,0:54:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.65,0:54:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm trying to help everybody out.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.29,0:54:07.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So you won't get mad anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.29,0:54:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Or upset about politics.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.29,0:54:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want you to realize they're all meerkats.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.29,0:54:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And the minute somebody says something you don't agree with.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.61,0:54:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You just go.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.13,0:54:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What's lady Clinton's first name?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.26,0:54:29.32,Default,,0,0,0,,What's her name? Hillary. Hillary.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.32,0:54:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hillary Clinton.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.34,0:54:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's boom-bom-bom-a.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.34,0:54:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Boom-bom-bom-a.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.22,0:54:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Hillary doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.22,0:54:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what from hot rock.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.98,0:54:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Obama's just wet behind the ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.13,0:54:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And Bush.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:56.98,0:55:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,God give me a break.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.65,0:55:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I think on Wikipedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:02.65,0:55:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Bush has more pages than anybody in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.18,0:55:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,That whole volume.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.66,0:55:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Bushism.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.66,0:55:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh God.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.98,0:55:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,How will the world recover?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.98,0:55:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Bushy.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.26,0:55:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean without Bush to beat on.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:20.26,0:55:22.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Who can we beat on?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.30,0:55:24.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't beat on a lady.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.30,0:55:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't beat on Hillary.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:27.00,0:55:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She's a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.00,0:55:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't beat on ladies.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.86,0:55:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And Obama's dark skin.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.75,0:55:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't beat on him either.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.52,0:55:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Who the hell can you beat on anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.55,0:55:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have racism.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.74,0:55:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And sexism.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.74,0:55:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.74,0:55:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem of races.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:48.78,0:55:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.78,0:55:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And nationalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.19,0:55:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I was.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.83,0:55:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,A full grown adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.83,0:55:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I realized that there was.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.83,0:56:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Prejudice against colored people.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.83,0:56:03.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The world I grew up in.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.83,0:56:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no such thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.83,0:56:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There were just people like everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.83,0:56:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.60,0:56:12.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody segmented them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.60,0:56:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,But according to race and color and nationality.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.60,0:56:16.60,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a great deal of segmentation.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.60,0:56:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,In many parts of the country.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.59,0:56:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,We always liked diversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.59,0:56:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason is we didn't call it diversity.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.88,0:56:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Polish guys told funny Polish jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.88,0:56:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jewish people told funny Jewish jokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.88,0:56:29.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And you wouldn't want to be without any of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.88,0:56:31.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Jewish people went away.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.88,0:56:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would you hear good Jewish jokes?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.17,0:56:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that short guy with the heavy Jewish accent?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.17,0:56:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,He's so funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.17,0:56:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.23,0:56:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Who would make such.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.23,0:56:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.23,0:56:46.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We never saw it as a negative.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.65,0:56:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only in the big city.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.65,0:56:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The social strata now changes all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.81,0:56:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.81,0:56:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got to change the color of the whole screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.81,0:56:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Social strata will change all of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.81,0:57:01.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What's appropriate at one level.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.16,0:57:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,At social society.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.16,0:57:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Is gross and inappropriate.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.16,0:57:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And vulgar at another.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:07.16,0:57:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Elvis Presley was vulgar.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.77,0:57:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.73,0:57:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So social strata.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.73,0:57:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,People don't like to think in terms of classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.73,0:57:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's not politically correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:18.76,0:57:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But on the other hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.76,0:57:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all they talk about.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.76,0:57:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Is social classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.76,0:57:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But they don't call it social classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.76,0:57:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All they're talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.98,0:57:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,In the so called.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.98,0:57:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,For ultra liberals.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.05,0:57:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is social.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.05,0:57:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All they're talking about all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.05,0:57:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Is social strata.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.05,0:57:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How they're pictured.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.05,0:57:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How they're viewed.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.05,0:57:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,How they're calibrated.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:45.05,0:57:47.08,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.08,0:57:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of this again is influenced by education.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.08,0:57:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And not the least bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.11,0:57:53.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Is also IQ.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.30,0:57:55.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So IQ when I grew up was important.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.30,0:57:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I always wanted to know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.30,0:57:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The school psychologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.30,0:58:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it had to do with vocational guidance.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.40,0:58:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If your IQ was sufficient.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.40,0:58:05.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You could make it in college.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:05.40,0:58:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,They guided you into an academic type of curriculum.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.40,0:58:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If your IQ wasn't high enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.43,0:58:11.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That you would be a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.43,0:58:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,In college.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.43,0:58:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They tried to steer you towards vocational.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.43,0:58:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Vocational.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.43,0:58:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.69,0:58:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know if that's done anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.69,0:58:23.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But vocational meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.69,0:58:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That you didn't have to study all this academic stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.69,0:58:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The great books of the western world.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.69,0:58:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,That memorized all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.69,0:58:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:31.69,0:58:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.69,0:58:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're working in a tool and dye shop.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.13,0:58:39.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And machinists.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.13,0:58:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I found out the hard way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.16,0:58:43.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Machinists make a lot of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.16,0:58:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a couple of things made.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.54,0:58:48.57,Default,,0,0,0,,For a big water wheel.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.57,0:58:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There were 400.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.57,0:58:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,These bearings were $400 a piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.57,0:58:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I said how much are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.57,0:58:56.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He said $400.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.66,0:58:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought he meant for the pair. He meant a piece.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.66,0:59:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,A large bearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.66,0:59:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,$400 to have it made by a machinist.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.66,0:59:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He made two of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.66,0:59:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're looking at $800.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.24,0:59:09.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.24,0:59:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The vocational.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.24,0:59:13.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The trades.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:13.24,0:59:15.30,Default,,0,0,0,,To my mind are equal.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.30,0:59:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you need somebody to help you with the trades.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.30,0:59:19.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You need it bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.30,0:59:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do without the thinker people.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.30,0:59:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do without the thinker people.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.30,0:59:25.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When you need it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.30,0:59:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When the plumbing is shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.30,0:59:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you fix the bloody thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.17,0:59:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you fix the bloody thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.17,0:59:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.71,0:59:36.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What channel is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.71,0:59:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,History channel anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.87,0:59:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ice truckers.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.87,0:59:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Ice road truckers.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:42.87,0:59:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,A whole society.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.87,0:59:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Up near north of Canada.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.87,0:59:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Trucking these giant monster trucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.87,0:59:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,In the winter time.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:50.87,0:59:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The lake freezes over.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.87,0:59:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can get up to the arctic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:54.87,0:59:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Where the big diamond mines are.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.87,0:59:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Three months out of the year.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.87,1:00:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,These truckers come from all over.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.87,1:00:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Drive these huge trucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.87,1:00:04.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And 24 inches of ice.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.87,1:00:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Not me thank you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.87,1:00:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But this monster truck.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.87,1:00:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Had nothing but this much ice under him.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.87,1:00:12.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can hear it cracking as he goes.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.87,1:00:14.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But he makes $1000 a trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:14.87,1:00:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,$1000 a trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.87,1:00:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.54,1:00:21.54,Default,,0,0,0,,At $1000 a trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.54,1:00:23.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess we won't joke about truckers anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.54,1:00:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't get $1000 a trip.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.54,1:00:27.54,Default,,0,0,0,,So.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.54,1:00:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Education and IQ.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.54,1:00:31.54,Default,,0,0,0,,But we tend to.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.54,1:00:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,This has certain meanings to us.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.54,1:00:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.54,1:00:37.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What we're talking about are values.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.54,1:00:39.54,Default,,0,0,0,,All these things now.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.54,1:00:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only exist in their own right.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.54,1:00:43.54,Default,,0,0,0,,First there's the reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.54,1:00:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's how they're viewed.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.64,1:00:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But then you have the value of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.64,1:00:49.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In some places.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.64,1:00:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Education is of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.64,1:00:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely required.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.64,1:00:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And high IQ.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.64,1:00:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Just happens to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.64,1:00:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,An accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.64,1:01:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A genetic accident.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.67,1:01:03.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And people admire a high IQ.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.67,1:01:05.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is a curse to those that are born with an extremely high IQ.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.67,1:01:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of them have to go for therapy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.67,1:01:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.07,1:01:14.62,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to go for therapy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.62,1:01:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they're not well adjusted.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.62,1:01:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Other people think in certain ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.62,1:01:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And they can't understand how they can think that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.62,1:01:22.62,Default,,0,0,0,,How can they think that way?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.62,1:01:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,How can they find that interesting?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.84,1:01:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Going around and around in a circle with a little rubber ball.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.84,1:01:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.51,1:01:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When you've got a new interpretation of Plato sitting next to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.51,1:01:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,How can that be?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.51,1:01:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.70,1:01:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The human dilemma.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:40.22,1:01:42.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So we talk about all these variable factors.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:42.22,1:01:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see they.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.22,1:01:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,If you put them together and recombine them.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.22,1:01:52.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We've already covered thousands of possibilities and variations in the human dilemma.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.22,1:01:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In the house of mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.31,1:01:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You see.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.31,1:01:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We're constantly walking through.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.31,1:02:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody. Anybody.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.31,1:02:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in the house of mirrors.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.66,1:02:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.66,1:02:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,More common than I.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.95,1:02:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Well you can get lost in there.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.95,1:02:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And they have to come and find you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.70,1:02:15.70,Default,,0,0,0,,They have to come and find you.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:15.70,1:02:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Well they can tell where you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.86,1:02:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they've got trackers now.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.86,1:02:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But it is of course constantly puzzling at every turn.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.86,1:02:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So every turn.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.86,1:02:25.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you begin to see things differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.86,1:02:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Every turn you see where you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:27.86,1:02:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In relationship to everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.86,1:02:31.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Differently.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.86,1:02:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see how complex human life is.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.93,1:02:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore we honor human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:35.93,1:02:37.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Because for any human being to walk on.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.93,1:02:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,To me.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.93,1:02:41.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Deserves admiration.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.93,1:02:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes a huge amount of will.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.06,1:02:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And devotion to life.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.06,1:02:48.06,Default,,0,0,0,,To just keep walking on.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:48.06,1:02:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,With your head up held high.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:50.06,1:02:52.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.60,1:02:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As we know are karmic propensities.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.60,1:02:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic propensities.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.60,1:02:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them are gifts of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.60,1:03:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.70,1:03:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of human life.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.70,1:03:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is really the evolution of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.70,1:03:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.95,1:03:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The capacity for the adaptational.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.95,1:03:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Stress to change is constant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.95,1:03:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,In our society.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.95,1:03:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing lasts very long.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.95,1:03:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's old hat.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.95,1:03:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's passe.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.95,1:03:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no longer in.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.95,1:03:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not even for sale anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.14,1:03:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Adaptational stress to change is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:25.14,1:03:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have to change with each.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:27.14,1:03:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Additional factor.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.14,1:03:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,With age you have to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.18,1:03:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,As you age.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.18,1:03:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to constantly change your expectations.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.18,1:03:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Your social roles.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.18,1:03:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're constantly shifting.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.18,1:03:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Your understanding of the interaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.18,1:03:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Of this enormous complexity.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.18,1:03:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.07,1:03:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.07,1:03:50.07,Default,,0,0,0,,On top of the stress of change.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.07,1:03:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We have different forms of government.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.07,1:03:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And they imply.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.07,1:03:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Different kinds of accountability.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.07,1:03:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Different forms of government.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.07,1:04:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And the constant argument.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:00.07,1:04:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Over which is the best form of government.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.07,1:04:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And how to define that government.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:04.07,1:04:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As it's defined.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.07,1:04:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the Senate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.07,1:04:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And the ruling.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:10.23,1:04:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Departments.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.39,1:04:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Of our country.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.39,1:04:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That is a constant.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.39,1:04:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Form of conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.39,1:04:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Every news every night.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.39,1:04:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Reflects some different.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:22.39,1:04:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Some conflict.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.39,1:04:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Having to do with government agencies.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.39,1:04:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course right now immigration.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.39,1:04:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And legality of immigration.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.52,1:04:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And all that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.55,1:04:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In the end however.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.55,1:04:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We know that we are accountable.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.62,1:04:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Spiritual responsibility.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:38.62,1:04:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Begins with the realization.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:40.62,1:04:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That you are accountable.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.62,1:04:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A person who will not accept.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.62,1:04:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal accountability.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:46.62,1:04:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Then is why they calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.62,1:04:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Extremely low.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.62,1:04:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's why atheists cannot do.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:52.62,1:04:54.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The muscle test for truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.62,1:04:57.77,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a famous professor.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.77,1:04:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That knocks it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.77,1:05:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And says it doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.77,1:05:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thought how come.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.77,1:05:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,He's such a famous professor.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.77,1:05:07.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And then I found out he calibrates 195.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.77,1:05:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Basically an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:09.77,1:05:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you deny the reality of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.77,1:05:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Then you're not allowed to benefit.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.77,1:05:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,From truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.77,1:05:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't benefit from that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.80,1:05:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Which you deny.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.80,1:05:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you especially.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.80,1:05:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,That which you denounce.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.34,1:05:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you denounce divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.34,1:05:28.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is the ultimate source of truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.70,1:05:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright so if you look at life.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.70,1:05:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see we have endless.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.70,1:05:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands and thousands of decisions.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.70,1:05:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,From second to second.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.05,1:05:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Now every.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.43,1:05:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Every branch in the tree.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.43,1:05:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can choose.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.50,1:05:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Every decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.04,1:05:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You make every second.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.04,1:05:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And you have to make them continuously.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:50.04,1:05:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You can either go in this direction.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.04,1:05:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You come to a why in the road.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:54.04,1:05:56.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I have an apple or not have an apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.04,1:05:58.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes or no.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.14,1:06:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If I have an apple.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.14,1:06:02.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I might get so and so.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.14,1:06:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Each one leads to another one.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.22,1:06:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright if you start out.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.22,1:06:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In the middle of ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.54,1:06:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Asking questions.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.54,1:06:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's say we calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:13.54,1:06:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Every decision you have to make.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.54,1:06:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I need more gas in the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.64,1:06:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes no.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.64,1:06:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If we calibrate every decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.77,1:06:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,If you always follow the yes answer.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.77,1:06:25.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You will end up.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.77,1:06:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Going up the tree this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.28,1:06:30.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I pay my income taxes on time.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.28,1:06:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I try and screw the government.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.28,1:06:34.89,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:34.89,1:06:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep going.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.89,1:06:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep choosing the yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.89,1:06:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The higher consciousness level.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:41.08,1:06:43.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You will end up in a completely.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:43.08,1:06:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Different place.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.08,1:06:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Than a person who always.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.14,1:06:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Chooses the no.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.50,1:06:51.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:51.50,1:06:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That following truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:53.50,1:06:55.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Will take you ultimately to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.94,1:06:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you do nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.94,1:06:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But know how to discern truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.94,1:07:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And follow the answer that is true every time.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:01.94,1:07:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You will automatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.94,1:07:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,End up through the decision tree process.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.94,1:07:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is continuous.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.94,1:07:09.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't even choose.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.94,1:07:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether to make decisions or not.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.94,1:07:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You are not free to make.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.23,1:07:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That choice.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.06,1:07:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,That you realize every second.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.06,1:07:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to make a decision.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:21.22,1:07:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Every second.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:23.74,1:07:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This very second.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.74,1:07:27.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I listen to what he is saying.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.74,1:07:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Shall I try to understand it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.74,1:07:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,It is too complex for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.74,1:07:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean life is simple.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:33.74,1:07:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Why put a lot of stuff together.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.18,1:07:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a reason not to even listen to myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:39.50,1:07:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,That is why I don't bother.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.50,1:07:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know what he is thinking.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.62,1:07:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It is irrelevant you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:45.62,1:07:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So we just keep following.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.30,1:07:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth to where.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:50.58,1:07:52.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth will lead you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.58,1:07:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you keep doing this continually.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.58,1:07:56.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you keep following.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.58,1:07:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:58.58,1:08:00.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you choose love over hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.58,1:08:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,If you choose humor over.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.58,1:08:04.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Mourningfulness etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.58,1:08:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You will automatically.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.58,1:08:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,End up with divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.58,1:08:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All roads lead to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:10.84,1:08:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,All roads lead to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.84,1:08:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So long as you take the right fork.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.84,1:08:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,If you take the wrong fork.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.86,1:08:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It leads elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.86,1:08:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't mention where.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.82,1:08:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Places you don't want to be.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.62,1:08:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth in other words.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.62,1:08:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is its own pathway to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.68,1:08:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 10,000 pathways to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.68,1:08:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.68,1:08:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Love, service, karma, yoga.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:38.68,1:08:40.68,Default,,0,0,0,,All the classic yogas etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:40.68,1:08:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The pathway of truth then.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.68,1:08:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Is for maybe an intellectual person.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:44.68,1:08:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Who just has to always have a word.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.68,1:08:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a description.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:48.68,1:08:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Or a definition.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:50.68,1:08:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they are not.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.68,1:08:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To the non-linear domain yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:54.68,1:08:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Where just lovingness.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.68,1:08:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Would be meaningful to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.78,1:09:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Lovingness like.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.78,1:09:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,How can you love such a SOB like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.78,1:09:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,So lovingness won't work for a lot of people.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.83,1:09:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the lovingness is in the 500's.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.83,1:09:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The person who is.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:09.86,1:09:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Just getting into the spiritual levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:11.86,1:09:13.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is not up to 200 yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:13.86,1:09:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,So by constantly following.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.86,1:09:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That which calibrates high.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:17.86,1:09:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,High versus low.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.86,1:09:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Following truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.86,1:09:23.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Like all roads lead to Rome.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.86,1:09:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth all roads.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.28,1:09:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Lead to God.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.60,1:09:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,To divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.66,1:09:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And if it doesn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.69,1:09:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Well.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.55,1:09:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess it leads you to the other place.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.55,1:09:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's helpful then.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.68,1:09:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,To recontextualize the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.68,1:09:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll just take a break in a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.68,1:09:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I want you to see everyone as a meerkat.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.68,1:09:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what the meerkats look like?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.54,1:10:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay meerkats.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.24,1:10:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see you after the break.
